translated: Jacobsson, Nils Jacob Johannes, lawyer, Gothenburg, born November 19th, 1911 in Oskarshamn to sea captain Uno J. and his wife Gunne Larsson. Children: Christer born 1937, Ann-Christine born 1939. Education: Studied at Gothenburg high school and latin school, graduated in 1931. Received a law degree at Uppsala University in 1935. Started working as a court clerk in Norrviken, and later worked in an attorney's office in Gothenburg. Became managing director of the company A-B Fören, Båtvarv. Has been a member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1939, and married his partner in the same year.
